Strickler Knob Trail is a 5.4 mile moderately trafficked out and back trail located near Luray, Virginia that features beautiful wild flowers and is rated as difficult. The trail is primarily used for hiking and bird watching and is accessible year-round.
LoudounEvents.EventAddress: Scothorn Gap Trail, 2354 US Hwy 340 N, Luray, VA 22835

LoudounEvents.EventDescription: Crabtree Falls Trail is a 2.8 mile heavily trafficked out and back trail located near Tyro, Virginia that features a waterfall and is rated as moderate. The trail offers a number of activity options and is accessible year-round. Dogs are also able to use this trail but must be kept on leash.
LoudounEvents.EventAddress: Crabtree Falls, 10438-, 10636 Crabtree Falls Hwy, Tyro, VA 22976

LoudounEvents.EventDescription: Signal Knob Loop Trail is a 10 mile heavily trafficked loop trail located near Strasburg, Virginia that features beautiful wild flowers and is rated as difficult. The trail is primarily used for hiking, running, bird watching, and horses and is best used from April until November. Dogs are also able to use this trail but must be kept on leash.
LoudounEvents.EventAddress: 11621 Fort Valley Rd, Fort Valley, VA 22652
